1
00:00:02,336 --> 00:00:12,346
["Carol of the Bells,"
ominous instrumental]

2
00:00:12,379 --> 00:00:22,524
["Carol of the Bells,"
ominous instrumental]

3
00:00:36,905 --> 00:00:38,773
-[narrator]
<i>Ah, there she is.</i>

4
00:00:38,806 --> 00:00:40,340
<i>Good old Hollywood.</i>

5
00:00:40,374 --> 00:00:42,510
<i>Sold as a land of dreams,</i>

6
00:00:42,544 --> 00:00:46,113
<i>this is a deeply backwards town</i>
<i>for the majority.</i>

7
00:00:46,146 --> 00:00:49,517
<i>Fablers and thespians flock</i>
<i>to the twinkling lights,</i>

8
00:00:49,551 --> 00:00:51,853
<i>where they fight</i>
<i>to make believe,</i>

9
00:00:51,886 --> 00:00:54,121
<i>until a select few rise up</i>

10
00:00:54,154 --> 00:00:57,291
<i>and metastasize</i>
<i>into the gatekeepers themselves.</i>

11
00:00:59,794 --> 00:01:03,297
<i>When some reach new heights,</i>
<i>they withhold a helping hand</i>

12
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:07,569
<i>and instead spit</i>
<i>on the fellow creatives below.</i>

13
00:01:11,806 --> 00:01:14,576
-[host] <i>Hey everyone, welcome</i>
<i>to</i> Entertainment Evening.

14
00:01:14,609 --> 00:01:17,110
<i>We have lots to unpack</i>
<i>for you tonight,</i>

15
00:01:17,144 --> 00:01:19,413
<i>including a red carpet</i>
<i>altercation...</i>

16
00:01:19,446 --> 00:01:21,015
-[narrator]
<i>But on Christmas Eve,</i>

17
00:01:21,049 --> 00:01:24,018
<i>a sextuplet</i>
<i>of struggling artists</i>

18
00:01:24,052 --> 00:01:26,554
<i>will have their fortunes altered</i>

19
00:01:26,588 --> 00:01:29,724
<i>by an unexpected</i>
<i>and mysterious holiday gift.</i>

20
00:01:29,757 --> 00:01:30,925
[banging on door]

21
00:01:30,959 --> 00:01:32,760
[door creaks open]

22
00:01:36,864 --> 00:01:38,666
[distant dog barking]

23
00:01:41,569 --> 00:01:44,404
-[Dame]
<i>Dear distinguished guest,</i>

24
00:01:44,438 --> 00:01:48,475
<i>you are cordially invited to...</i>

25
00:01:48,509 --> 00:01:51,211
-[Princess] ... <i>a remarkable</i>
<i>and exclusive evening</i>

26
00:01:51,244 --> 00:01:54,381
<i>that will forever</i>
<i>change your life.</i>

27
00:01:55,516 --> 00:01:58,185
[screams]

28
00:01:58,218 --> 00:02:00,622
-[Spaceman]
<i>Enclosed is your golden ticket.</i>

29
00:02:00,655 --> 00:02:05,325
-[Cowboy] <i>And a $1,000 preview</i>
<i>of a fortune to be had.</i>

30
00:02:05,359 --> 00:02:07,394
[laughs]

31
00:02:07,427 --> 00:02:09,964
-[Ghost] <i>Inscribed on the ticket</i>
<i>is your pseudonym,</i>

32
00:02:09,998 --> 00:02:12,600
<i>call time, and address.</i>

33
00:02:12,634 --> 00:02:14,167
<i>You are Ghost.</i>

34
00:02:19,507 --> 00:02:22,043
[phone pings]

35
00:02:22,076 --> 00:02:23,645
["Deck the Halls" on radio]

36
00:02:23,678 --> 00:02:25,647
-[radio DJ] <i>Lastly, there are</i>
<i>three rules for the event.</i>

37
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,214
<i>Don't bring cell phones,</i>

38
00:02:27,247 --> 00:02:29,050
<i>don't discuss</i>
<i>your personal lives</i>

39
00:02:29,083 --> 00:02:30,852
<i>and don't be late.</i>

40
00:02:30,885 --> 00:02:32,219
<i>See you tonight.</i>

41
00:02:32,252 --> 00:02:34,354
-I bet some pretty famous people
Uber up here, yeah?

42
00:02:34,388 --> 00:02:36,991
-They don't ride UberPool.

43
00:02:37,025 --> 00:02:40,394
-[awkward chuckle]
Right. Right.

44
00:02:40,427 --> 00:02:43,798
Right.
♪ <i>Fa-la-la-la-la, la-la-la-la!</i> ♪

45
00:02:43,831 --> 00:02:47,234
Hey, what's the craziest thing
you've seen while driving?

46
00:02:47,267 --> 00:02:49,436
Okay, okay, I got one.
[clears throat]

47
00:02:49,469 --> 00:02:51,939
I once saw a pigeon fly out
of a woman's bag.

48
00:02:51,973 --> 00:02:53,074
Now this is a true story.

49
00:02:53,107 --> 00:02:54,374
So I'm sitting up here
in the front seat.

50
00:02:54,408 --> 00:02:55,810
Now, two women
who don't know each other

51
00:02:55,843 --> 00:02:56,944
are sittin' in the back.

52
00:02:56,978 --> 00:02:58,646
Now, grocery bag lady
falls asleep,

53
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:00,515
and no sooner does she do that
than bang!

54
00:03:00,548 --> 00:03:02,884
A pigeon flies out,
and this guy is flapping,

55
00:03:02,917 --> 00:03:05,086
and he is going crazy.

56
00:03:05,119 --> 00:03:06,788
And the old lady sitting
next to her,

57
00:03:06,821 --> 00:03:08,623
she grabs the pigeon,

58
00:03:08,656 --> 00:03:11,159
snaps the bird's neck
real casual,

59
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:13,061
and puts it right back
into the grocery bag.

60
00:03:13,094 --> 00:03:15,429
And the craziest part
about this

61
00:03:15,462 --> 00:03:18,465
is grocery lady
never even woke up.

62
00:03:20,134 --> 00:03:21,334
Made me realize
how much we miss

63
00:03:21,368 --> 00:03:24,038
just by closing our eyes.

64
00:03:24,072 --> 00:03:26,941
-Shit...I remember
that monologue

65
00:03:26,974 --> 00:03:29,777
from Leonard Kahn's class.

66
00:03:29,811 --> 00:03:30,912
-What are you talking about?

67
00:03:30,945 --> 00:03:33,047
-Yeah, went there in 2017.

68
00:03:33,081 --> 00:03:34,749
Did the same monologue.

69
00:03:34,782 --> 00:03:35,817
You're good.

70
00:03:35,850 --> 00:03:37,952
You gotta slow it down though.

71
00:03:37,985 --> 00:03:39,554
-Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

72
00:03:42,123 --> 00:03:44,391
On, um, on which part?

73
00:03:44,424 --> 00:03:46,561
[car tires screech]

74
00:03:46,594 --> 00:03:49,097
Thank you for the invitation
to...

75
00:03:49,130 --> 00:03:52,633
Thank you. Thank you.

76
00:03:52,667 --> 00:03:56,436
[foreboding music]

77
00:03:58,371 --> 00:04:01,809
Good day. Thank you so much
for this surprise invitation

78
00:04:01,843 --> 00:04:04,011
to your humble abode.

79
00:04:04,045 --> 00:04:04,979
No one says that.

80
00:04:05,012 --> 00:04:07,615
[doorbell rings]

81
00:04:07,648 --> 00:04:10,151
Hello. Good day.
It's nice to meet you.

82
00:04:10,184 --> 00:04:12,486
It's nice to be
at your sophisticated

83
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,254
and yet humble abode.

84
00:04:14,287 --> 00:04:16,057
-Mm-hm. You're late
and you sound Mormon.

85
00:04:16,090 --> 00:04:18,126
-Yeah. No, no, no.

86
00:04:18,159 --> 00:04:20,260
Sorry.
My--my driver dropped me off

87
00:04:20,293 --> 00:04:22,597
-a little bit down the road.
-Oh!

88
00:04:24,031 --> 00:04:25,265
He doesn't have it.

89
00:04:25,298 --> 00:04:26,501
-Oh no, no.
No, no. I have it.

90
00:04:26,534 --> 00:04:28,368
-[Dame] The card?
-Yeah, I have it.

91
00:04:28,401 --> 00:04:31,404
Yeah, it says--it says--
it says I'm a Hero.

92
00:04:32,305 --> 00:04:34,374
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Oh!

93
00:04:34,407 --> 00:04:36,077
-All right, hold on.

94
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:37,545
Read the sign.
Wipe your hooves.

95
00:04:37,578 --> 00:04:40,047
-Oh. Yeah.

96
00:04:41,149 --> 00:04:42,650
It's a little tarpy
in here though.

97
00:04:42,683 --> 00:04:46,187
-Yeah, a lot of tarps.
Very <i>American Psycho</i> .

98
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:48,089
-Whooh. Yeah, I'll say.

99
00:04:48,122 --> 00:04:49,524
-Hey.
-[Hero] Hello, everyone.

100
00:04:49,557 --> 00:04:52,459
-Here. Drink this,
but drink it slowly.

101
00:04:52,492 --> 00:04:54,562
We don't have a lot
of alcohol here.

102
00:04:56,363 --> 00:05:00,067
Okay, guys, this is Hero.

103
00:05:00,101 --> 00:05:02,069
He's late.
Hero, this is everyone.

104
00:05:02,103 --> 00:05:03,370
They've been waiting.

105
00:05:03,403 --> 00:05:04,806
Go ahead,
introduce yourselves.

106
00:05:04,839 --> 00:05:07,275
-My card says I'm a Ghost,
but I'm not a ghost.

107
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:09,409
-Yeah, no, I'm the spaceman.
-[Hero] Great.

108
00:05:09,442 --> 00:05:11,478
-I was a <i>goat</i> , though,
in a past life in Scotland.

109
00:05:11,512 --> 00:05:13,514
No, but I'm here
in front of you right now.

110
00:05:13,548 --> 00:05:17,450
-Hi. Princess.
-Howdy. Cowboy.

111
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:19,386
-And I'm the Dame.

112
00:05:19,419 --> 00:05:22,757
-So, uh, you coordinate
this rendezvous?

113
00:05:22,790 --> 00:05:26,828
-No. No, I--I wish.

114
00:05:26,861 --> 00:05:29,630
-[Princess] Well,
this is it then. Us six.

115
00:05:29,664 --> 00:05:32,900
-Oh, and how do you know that?

116
00:05:32,934 --> 00:05:34,635
-There's six chairs.

117
00:05:34,669 --> 00:05:36,771
-[Hero] Right.
Okay, right, that--

118
00:05:36,804 --> 00:05:40,308
yeah, math checks out,
everybody.

119
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,910
Um, so does anybody know
each other, or is-

120
00:05:42,944 --> 00:05:43,811
-No.
-Nope.

121
00:05:43,845 --> 00:05:45,412
-[Dame] Mm-mm.
-No one knows anything,

122
00:05:45,445 --> 00:05:47,548
but clearly this is a game show.

123
00:05:47,582 --> 00:05:49,116
So I just want
to put out right now,

124
00:05:49,150 --> 00:05:50,585
when we do split up into teams,

125
00:05:50,618 --> 00:05:52,086
I just want to let you know
that I'm very lucky.

126
00:05:52,119 --> 00:05:53,788
I'm unusually lucky.

127
00:05:53,821 --> 00:05:56,657
Like, every dog I've ever known
has lived more than 15 years.

128
00:05:56,691 --> 00:05:58,559
Fifteen years! Ha!
That's unheard of.

129
00:05:58,593 --> 00:06:00,094
-I doubt it's a game show.

130
00:06:00,127 --> 00:06:02,330
-Maybe this is a cult thing.

131
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:04,364
-Honestly, I thought it
was another intervention.

132
00:06:04,397 --> 00:06:05,867
So I've already won.

133
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:08,002
-You know, they might
be single-filin' us

134
00:06:08,035 --> 00:06:10,137
through that Great Blue Door.

135
00:06:10,171 --> 00:06:11,438
-[Princess] Hmm?
-Uh--

136
00:06:11,471 --> 00:06:14,609
-A Blue Door is a cow's entrance
to a slaughterhouse.

137
00:06:14,642 --> 00:06:16,711
-See, they don't know
where they are

138
00:06:16,744 --> 00:06:18,478
before they get popped
right between the eyes.

139
00:06:18,512 --> 00:06:19,479
[imitates eye popping]

140
00:06:19,513 --> 00:06:21,249
[distant ringing]
-Ah!

141
00:06:21,282 --> 00:06:23,450
Hang on, what is that?

142
00:06:23,483 --> 00:06:24,585
-What is that?

143
00:06:24,619 --> 00:06:25,820
-Come on.
Hey, hey, hey, guys, come on.

144
00:06:25,853 --> 00:06:27,755
Rule number one
on the invite is no cells.

145
00:06:27,788 --> 00:06:29,590
-[Cowboy] You brought your
cell phone with you, didn't you?

146
00:06:29,624 --> 00:06:30,992
-No, you saw me leaving
the apartment.

147
00:06:31,025 --> 00:06:32,627
-Then what's ringing?
Is it in your sock?

148
00:06:32,660 --> 00:06:33,527
-Did you bring your phone?
-It's not my fucking phone!

149
00:06:33,561 --> 00:06:35,162
-I didn't bring my phone.

150
00:06:35,196 --> 00:06:36,731
-Okay, rule number two is don't
talk about your personal lives.

151
00:06:36,764 --> 00:06:38,532
What--what is happening
right now?

152
00:06:38,566 --> 00:06:41,434
-Well, you--you--you did say
the dog thing.

153
00:06:41,468 --> 00:06:42,570
-[Ghost]
But dog's not the same thing.

154
00:06:42,603 --> 00:06:43,604
-Dog is not personal life.
-[Dame] Quiet!

155
00:06:43,638 --> 00:06:44,939
-All right, well,
he's my brother.

156
00:06:44,972 --> 00:06:46,707
-He's always up my ass.
-[indistinct] telling them--

157
00:06:46,741 --> 00:06:47,808
-They would have figured it out
eventually.

158
00:06:47,842 --> 00:06:49,210
I don't know
what you want from me.

159
00:06:49,243 --> 00:06:50,244
-You got to shut your gizzard.

160
00:06:50,278 --> 00:06:51,279
-Jesus Christ.
-Everyone, shut up!

161
00:06:51,312 --> 00:06:53,014
-Listen.
-Shut up!

162
00:06:53,047 --> 00:06:55,249
[device ringing]

163
00:06:55,283 --> 00:06:57,151
-God, it's still sealed.
-Is it in there?

164
00:06:57,184 --> 00:06:58,152
-Oh, wait.

165
00:06:58,185 --> 00:07:00,888
[device ringing]

166
00:07:06,594 --> 00:07:08,162
-What does the card say?

167
00:07:08,195 --> 00:07:11,165
-"Saddle up for a wild night."

168
00:07:12,767 --> 00:07:15,770
[woman vocalizing
"Carol of the Bells"]

169
00:07:20,574 --> 00:07:23,244
-Think someone's supposed
to come in?

170
00:07:23,277 --> 00:07:25,478
-Yeah, right.

171
00:07:25,513 --> 00:07:26,948
Well, you missed your cue.

172
00:07:26,981 --> 00:07:29,617
[chuckles] Saddle up.

173
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:31,752
Nobody?
Come on, come on.

174
00:07:31,786 --> 00:07:33,321
That was an amateur clue.

175
00:07:33,354 --> 00:07:34,922
Any of you guys could have made
a better clue than that clue.

176
00:07:34,956 --> 00:07:36,857
-Maybe there's something
under one of our chairs.

177
00:07:36,891 --> 00:07:39,360
-Maybe it's like a sexual thing

178
00:07:39,393 --> 00:07:40,995
and we're supposed
to partner off?

179
00:07:41,028 --> 00:07:42,330
[laughter]

180
00:07:42,363 --> 00:07:44,131
-[Dame] Oh, my God.
-What?

181
00:07:44,165 --> 00:07:46,634
-[Cowboy] Fun fact, he actually
took dialect classes

182
00:07:46,667 --> 00:07:48,202
to get rid of his accent,

183
00:07:48,235 --> 00:07:49,971
but he does call
in reservations

184
00:07:50,004 --> 00:07:51,072
as Matthew McConaughey.

185
00:07:51,105 --> 00:07:52,406
-Oh God, why?

186
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,474
-Because this town
is chock-full of smug folk,

187
00:07:54,508 --> 00:07:55,710
and it is my way
of keeping pace.

188
00:07:55,743 --> 00:07:57,011
-[Princess] How clever.

189
00:07:57,044 --> 00:07:58,813
I mean, I just assumed
we're all in the industry.

190
00:07:58,846 --> 00:08:01,082
-[Hero] You're actress?
-Yeah.

191
00:08:01,115 --> 00:08:03,584
But I just dropped my manager,

192
00:08:03,617 --> 00:08:06,520
and I'm actually saving up
for some new headshots, so-

193
00:08:06,554 --> 00:08:07,855
-[Ghost] All right.

194
00:08:07,888 --> 00:08:09,657
I bet I could guess
everybody's jobs.

195
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:11,659
-[Dame] So,
overconfident producer?

196
00:08:11,692 --> 00:08:12,994
-[Hero] Wait, wait, guys.

197
00:08:13,027 --> 00:08:15,663
I don't think we should be
talking about our lives.

198
00:08:15,696 --> 00:08:18,733
-Okay. So, producer, actress...

199
00:08:18,766 --> 00:08:21,836
-Hm.
-Writer, and...

200
00:08:21,869 --> 00:08:22,670
directing duo.

201
00:08:22,703 --> 00:08:23,738
-Mm. Nope.
-Yeah.

202
00:08:23,771 --> 00:08:25,206
-[Dame]
Who never agree on anything.

203
00:08:25,239 --> 00:08:28,409
-Yeah.
And actor.

204
00:08:28,442 --> 00:08:33,114
-Ha! No.
-Bad actor.

205
00:08:33,147 --> 00:08:37,485
-No, listen, you don't know
anything about me.

206
00:08:37,518 --> 00:08:38,552
-Who has thin skin.

207
00:08:38,586 --> 00:08:39,820
-Okay, fuck off.

208
00:08:39,854 --> 00:08:41,088
-[laughs]

209
00:08:42,523 --> 00:08:44,258
-[clears throat]
Let's figure out what, uh,

210
00:08:44,291 --> 00:08:45,593
saddle up means.

211
00:08:45,626 --> 00:08:48,162
-It doesn't have anything to do
with the chairs.

212
00:08:48,195 --> 00:08:49,296
-The welcome mat!

213
00:08:49,330 --> 00:08:51,565
-Jesus!
-Oh! The welcome mat!

214
00:08:51,599 --> 00:08:52,666
-We're all idiots.

215
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:53,667
-You want another one of these?

216
00:08:53,701 --> 00:08:55,436
-Yeah, fill her up.
-All right.

217
00:08:55,469 --> 00:08:56,704
-[Hero] The welcome mat.
The welcome mat.

218
00:08:56,737 --> 00:09:00,307
It's the welcome mat.
It's, um--oh, okay.

219
00:09:02,443 --> 00:09:04,578
"Wipe your hooves!"

220
00:09:04,612 --> 00:09:07,481
Oh! Guys, it says
"Getting warmer."

221
00:09:07,516 --> 00:09:09,617
Getting warmer.
Getting warmer.

222
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:12,653
-Getting warmer.
Oh, they got a barbecue.

223
00:09:12,686 --> 00:09:13,954
Smokehouse out back.

224
00:09:13,988 --> 00:09:16,123
-[murmurs] Warmer.
The sun. The sun.

225
00:09:16,157 --> 00:09:17,892
The solar eclipse?

226
00:09:17,925 --> 00:09:20,461
-Riddles are my nightmare.
-Fireplace.

227
00:09:20,494 --> 00:09:21,395
-[Spaceman]
I was just going to say that.

228
00:09:21,429 --> 00:09:23,297
-The fireplace. Yes.

229
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:24,432
That's brilliant.

230
00:09:24,465 --> 00:09:27,635
Oh my- That's it.
That's it. Yes.

231
00:09:28,769 --> 00:09:33,307
Um, oh, there's, uh...
there's nothing.

232
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:34,742
-Look under the logs.

233
00:09:34,775 --> 00:09:35,910
-What?
-Here. Try this.

234
00:09:35,943 --> 00:09:37,445
-You're going to love it.
-Thank God.

235
00:09:37,478 --> 00:09:38,913
-The thingy under the logs.

236
00:09:38,946 --> 00:09:41,949
-No. There's--there's--
there's nothing in-

237
00:09:43,717 --> 00:09:46,153
Holy shit. It's a safe.

238
00:09:46,187 --> 00:09:47,188
-How did you see that?

239
00:09:47,221 --> 00:09:48,622
-[Cowboy] What kind of safe?

240
00:09:49,490 --> 00:09:52,626
[safe beeping]

241
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:54,028
-[Hero]
